OL,3,CLondon jumps into top 10 in global
OL,4,C'most expensive cities' list
OL,6,FThe index includes 226 locations
OL,7,Facross the world. It measures the
OL,8,Fcomparative cost of more than 200
OL,9,Fitems in each location, including
OL,10,Ftransport, food, clothing, household
OL,11,Fgoods and entertainment.
OL,13,FAbuja in Nigeria was ranked least
OL,14,Fexpensive in the survey, at number 226.
OL,16,FMercer, a business of Marsh McLennan,
OL,17,Fcompiles the ranking to help
OL,18,Fmultinational employers plan
OL,19,Fcompensation packages for workers.
